            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Test 3 has the highest overall max RMS, indicating the strongest peak vibration severity across the three tests.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Test 1 has the highest overall max kurtosis, suggesting the strongest impulsive or shock-like behaviour.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Test 3 runs the longest, while Test 2 reaches strong degradation over a much shorter duration.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Bearing 3 is the dominant degradation case in Tests 1 and 3, while Bearing 1 is dominant in Test 2.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Normalised progress allows all three tests to be compared fairly despite their different durations.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
